### Configure Babel for Reanimated Web Support

Source: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/4.1.5/packages/docs-reanimated/docs/guides/web-support.mdx

Adds the necessary Babel plugins, `@babel/plugin-proposal-export-namespace-from` and `react-native-worklets/plugin`, to your `babel.config.js` file. Ensure the Reanimated plugin is listed last.

```javascript
module.exports = {
    presets: [
      // ...
    ],
    plugins: [
        // ...
        '@babel/plugin-proposal-export-namespace-from',
        'react-native-worklets/plugin',
    ],
};

```

--------------------------------

### Configure Babel Plugin for Reanimated

Source: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/4.1.5/packages/docs-reanimated/versioned_docs/version-2.x/fundamentals/installation.md

Adds the react-native-reanimated/plugin to the babel.config.js file. This plugin is essential for Reanimated to function correctly. It should typically be listed last in the plugins array.

```javascript
module.exports = {
    presets: [
      ...
    ],
    plugins: [
      ...
      'react-native-reanimated/plugin',
    ],
  };
```

--------------------------------

### Reanimated Babel Plugin Configuration in babel.config.js

Source: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/4.1.5/packages/docs-reanimated/docs/reanimated-babel-plugin/options.md

Demonstrates how to configure the react-native-reanimated Babel plugin within the babel.config.js file. This involves specifying the plugin and passing an options object to customize its behavior, such as enabling relative source locations and inline style warnings.

```javascript
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    // ... other plugins
    [
      'react-native-worklets/plugin',
      {
        relativeSourceLocation: true,
        disableInlineStylesWarning: true,
        omitNativeOnlyData: true,
        globals: ['myObjectOnUI'],
        substituteWebPlatformChecks: true,
      },
    ],
  ],
};
```

--------------------------------

### Create and Set Up Expo App for Testing

Source: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/4.1.5/packages/react-native-reanimated/RELEASE.md

Creates a new Expo application and configures it to test the local build of React Native Reanimated. This involves adding the local package, setting up Babel configuration, and copying example code.

```bash
npx create-expo-app my-app
yarn add ~/Downloads/react-native-reanimated-x.y.z.tgz
# If babel.config.js does not exist, create it using Expo Docs instructions.
# Add plugins: ['react-native-worklets/plugin'] to babel.config.js
# Copy Bokeh Example to App.tsx or index.tsx (for expo-router)
```

### Getting started > Installation > React Native Community CLI

Source: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/4.1.5/packages/docs-worklets/docs/fundamentals/getting-started.mdx

When using the React Native Community CLI, you need to manually add the `react-native-worklets/plugin` to your `babel.config.js`. This plugin automatically converts special JavaScript functions (called worklets) to allow them to be passed and run on the Worklet Runtimes. This plugin is included by default in Expo starter templates since Expo SDK 54.

